
Overview of noun crucifixion

The noun crucifixion has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (1) crucifixion -- (the act of executing by a method widespread in the ancient world; the victim's hands and feet are bound or nailed to a cross)
2. Crucifixion -- (the death of Jesus by crucifixion)
3. crucifixion, excruciation -- (the infliction of extremely painful punishment or suffering)
